items.preText: Hanushanth kuma: "Now 300 is well on after the back to back sixes. Game on Guys."
items.text: moves across, but a tad too early, Mashrafe follows him and concedes only a leg-bye to short fine leg
items.shortText: Mashrafe Mortaza to Williams, 1 leg bye

items.text: a wide full toss, slapped towards deep extra cover, protection there
smashed! Gives himself room and hits it hard, through extra cover. It was another length ball from Mashrafe, you cannot bowl those at this stage of the innings. A big over that one for Zimbabwe
items.shortText: Mashrafe Mortaza to Williams, FOUR runs

items.text: full and wide and Moor fails to get bat on that
items.shortText: Abu Hider to Moor, no run

items.preText: Azweer: "Zimbabwe fans wants MORE SIXES from MOOR..." -- I see what you tried to do there
items.text: fuller outside off, driven towards mid-off for one

items.preText: Back2BackCentur: "I sense a batting collapse from Bangladesh here."
items.text: in the slot, almost a nothing ball, fuller around off and Williams lofts it over wide long-on for his first six of the innings
items.shortText: Abu Hider to Williams, SIX runs

items.text: slower one outside off, Williams waits for it before smashing it towards long-off

items.preText: Eric: "Anybody has a calculator? I am quite ouzzled by Mash's handling of bowlers. Him bringing himself on right now means that Abu Haider cannot finish his full quota! He did the same during the Asia cup and its quite perplexing"
items.text: a full toss, Moor was looking to play it on the leg side, gets an outside edge towards third man, Hider would consider himself lucky there

items.preText: Adnan mahmud: "With all due respect, it should be clear to Mash by now that he is not death over bowler."
items.text: length ball, around middle, a short-arm pull from Williams towards deep midwicket, one bounce to the fielder

items.preText: These two have added 45 off 29 now
items.text: fuller outside off, steered towards deep backward point for one

items.preText: Subhayan: "Would love to see another thrilling match ending in a tie - A Neutral Fan"
items.text: a slower bouncer, Moor had to delay his pull there but still gets two to deep square leg
in the blockhole, Moor jams his bat at it to dig it out towards long-on

items.preText: Amir: "I think Mash was adjusting so that Saifuddin bowls the last over. "
items.text: another slower one, Williams moves across and helps it past short fine leg
items.shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Williams, FOUR runs

items.text: fuller outside off, smashed towards deep extra cover and Moor had to put in the dive. Perhaps a stronger and better throw was required

another slower bouncer and Williams forehands it towards deep extra cover, was in the air for a long time but lands safely as the batsmen come back for the second. This is turning out to be a really good knock by Williams
full, almost yorker-length outside off, Moor fails to connect there
items.shortText: Abu Hider to Moor, no run

items.text: is that out? It was one again full and Moor drilled it right back at the bowler who stuck his left hand out and the ball cannoned back into the stumps at the non-striker's end. But replays confirm Williams got his bat down just in time
items.shortText: Abu Hider to Moor, no run

items.text: fuller on the pads and clipped away towards deep square leg

items.preText: James: "Pretty good recovery by Zim from 7/2 after the first 5 overs."
items.text: goes for the reverse paddle, it was full outside off but Williams failed to connect
items.shortText: Abu Hider to Williams, no run

items.text: fuller again, Williams clears his front leg but doesn't get the timing right on this one, a single to long-on
fuller on stumps once again, Moor can also dig it out towards long-on
full and straight, Moor hits it hard, the ball hits the foot of the bowler and deflects towards long-off

a high full toss but Williams fails to take advantage of it, ends up skying it towards long-on, falls short of the fielder but a direct at the non-striker's end results in a run-out. Moor put in the dive but was well short
items.shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Williams, 1 run, OUT

dismissal.text: PJ Moor run out (Ariful Haque) 28 (21b 0x4 2x6) SR: 133.33

items.preText: Elton Chigumbura is the new man in, but right now he is at the non-striker's end
items.text: a slower one outside off, Williams looks to go big but misses
items.shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Williams, no run

items.text: slower bouncer, pulled towards deep midwicket but no power behind that
